the provisions of this Act or any  other law for the time being in force, where a company is required to re -
state it s financial  statements due to fraud or non -compliance with any requirement under this Act and the 
rules  made thereunder, the company shall recover from any past or present managing director or  whole -
time director or manager or Chief Executive Officer (by w hatever name called) who,  during the period for 
which the financial statements are required to be re -stated, received the  remuneration (including stock 
option) in excess of what would have been payable to him as  per restatement of financial statements.

